Risk Manager Job (Financial Services), Jakarta, Indonesia - PT Monroe Consulting Group
Risk Manager Job (Financial Services), Jakarta, Indonesia  -
Risk Manager Job (Financial Services), Jakarta, Indonesia
Responsibilities
Monroe Consulting Group is recruiting on behalf of an expanding Financing Holdings Company within the financial service industry in Indonesia. Our respected client is seeking a candidate with management experience for the job of Risk Manager, to be based in Jakarta, Indonesia. The winning candidate will mainly be responsible for credit analysis across the firm as well as ongoing credit review of an existing portfolio of counterparties to ensure that they are consistent with the Companys’ credit policies and risk appetite.  The winning candidate will report directly to the CFO part of the SME division. Key job responsibilities include: Credit analysis and review of a portfolio of creditsAnalyze, structure and approve transactions within existing limitsPreparation of credit proposals and reviewing documentationProviding recommendations and highlighting risk issues to front office and senior approversMonitoring market developments to assess credit quality of counterpartiesResponsible for the end-to-end credit review and analysis. As part of the team, will perform due diligence of small and medium enterprises and legal documentation to form a view of exposure being proposed that is in line with the companys’ credit policySupervise team in all components of ERM and/or risk management methodologies including risk diagnostics, identification, quantification, policies and procedures, monitoring, corporate governance and reporting, and risk systems  Job Requirements  Bachelor’s degree in finance or business major from a reputable universityAt least 5 years’ experience, with some supervisory experienceRelevant work experience in Risk covering areas such as Credit Risk, Market Risk, Operational Risk or Liquidity Risk. Includes knowledge of the risk tools and processes within a specific risk area including risk diagnostics, policies and procedures, industry best practices;  risk assessment, key driver analysis, risk quantification and modelling5+ years working in the Financial Services Industry such as in Banking, Capital Market, and/or InsuranceStrong understanding of Risk related Regulatory Requirements, such as Basel II/III, Solvency II, IFRS/IAS, AML/FraudUnderstanding of Lending Value Chain and Operations (both Front & Back Office) within Retail and Commercial BankingExcellent communication and facilitation skillsEffective team management and leadership skillsDetailed and accurateImplementing and enhancing internal controls over all aspects of the operations.Leadership ability and time management skillsAbility to solve practical problems and carry out responsibility under general and little supervisionAble to work under pressure, meet deadline and teamwork.Availability to work overtime, particularly around the month-end closeAbility to work well under pressure and balance multiple priorities. All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence. If you are a suitable match for this position please send your application to banking@monroeconsulting.com
